==Demographics==
At the [[2020 United States Census|2020 census]] there were 147 people, 32 households, and 24 families living in the CDP.  The population density was 178 people per square mile. There were 42 housing units.

The median household income was $20,620. The per capita income for the CDP was $11,415.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arizona.hometownlocator.com/az/pima/cowlic.cfm |publisher=Arizona.hometownlocator.com |access-date=2021-08-25 |date=2021 |title=Cowlic, AZ Profile: Facts & Data}}</ref>

